race.comment: Maher trained KIPPIS (11) has been kept fresh since his narrow defeat here on debut. Was heavily bet and has been kept up to the mark with a Cranbourne trial placing. Has Dee up and is the one they have to beat. COVERT MISSION (1) resumes, and on what we've seen the colt is a threat. Was on speed beaten 1L at Sandown-Hillside on debut and won a recent Mornington jumpout. Noonan rides and has been with him all along. IN'KANTOSSTAR (3) debuts for Maher with Ben Allen engaged. He's a full brother to multiple Group 1 winning sprinter Jimmysstar and is likely to have plenty of ability. Better for two jumpouts, and the betting will be key. SALARIA (14) had been well educated before a 2L defeat at Pakenham on debut. Loses Noonan but is in the mix.
